            <strong>Tech Stack:</strong> Python · FastAPI · LangGraph · CrewAI · OpenAI Agents SDK · Claude API (Anthropic) · MCP (Model Context Protocol) · Telegram Bot API · WhatsApp Business API · ChromaDB · Redis · pgvector · PostgreSQL · Playwright · Docker · AWS Bedrock · ReactJS · WebSocket Streaming · Guardrails AI · LangSmith
          </p>
          <p class="job-summary">Inspired by OpenClaw's agentic architecture — built a production-grade, message-driven multi-agent platform that converts natural-language instructions from messaging channels into decomposed, executable task plans using stateful AI agents.</p>
          <ul class="job-bullets">
            <li><strong>AGENTIC CORE:</strong> Designed a LangGraph-based orchestration engine that receives messages via Telegram/WhatsApp, decomposes high-level goals into structured sub-tasks, and assigns each sub-task to specialized agents (Researcher, Executor, Validator, Summarizer) — mirroring OpenClaw's 4-tier architecture.</li>
            <li><strong>MCP INTEGRATION:</strong> Implemented Model Context Protocol (MCP) to expose business tools (calendar, email, file system, shell commands) as discoverable agent capabilities; agents dynamically invoke tools based on task context without hardcoded logic.</li>
            <li><strong>MULTI-AGENT ORCHESTRATION:</strong> Built CrewAI-based role-based agent teams for domain tasks — Finance Agent crew for report generation, DevOps Agent crew for deployment validation, and Research Agent crew for real-time web data gathering using browser automation (Playwright).</li>
            <li><strong>PERSISTENT MEMORY:</strong> Layered agent memory — Redis short-term session context, ChromaDB vector store for long-term semantic recall, pgvector structured knowledge retrieval — agents remember user preferences and past task outcomes across sessions.</li>
            <li><strong>REAL-TIME STREAMING:</strong> WebSocket streaming response layer so users see agent reasoning steps and task progress live in the Telegram/WhatsApp interface as tasks execute.</li>
            <li><strong>AI SECURITY LAYER:</strong> Integrated Guardrails AI for prompt-injection detection, role-based tool permission enforcement, and human-in-the-loop approval gates for high-risk actions (code deployment, file deletion) — preventing agent hijacking attacks.</li>
            <li><strong>OBSERVABILITY:</strong> Wired LangSmith for full agent trace logging, tool-call auditing, latency tracking, and token cost dashboards; alerting via Slack webhook for failed agent workflows.</li>
            <li><strong>RESULT:</strong> End-to-end agent workflow (message received → task decomposed → agents executed → result returned) completes in under 8 seconds for standard 3-step tasks; system handles 200+ concurrent agent sessions on a 2-vCPU AWS EC2 instance.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <!-- Portfolio Project 2025 -->
