          </p>
          <p class="job-summary">Production-grade RAG platform purpose-built for Singapore's financial and legal sectors — ingests complex documents (PDPA policies, MAS circulars, loan agreements, annual reports) and delivers precise, cited AI answers with stateful multi-turn reasoning.</p>
          <ul class="job-bullets">
            <li><strong>ADVANCED RAG PIPELINE:</strong> Built hybrid search RAG — Pinecone dense vector + BM25 keyword with Cohere Rerank cross-encoder reranking — achieving <strong>94% answer relevancy</strong> on financial document QA benchmarks vs 71% with naive RAG.</li>
            <li><strong>LANGGRAPH REASONING:</strong> Stateful reasoning loop — agent first classifies query intent, decides whether to retrieve-then-generate or decompose into multi-hop sub-queries, executes retrieval, validates source confidence, then synthesizes a cited answer with source footnotes.</li>
            <li><strong>MULTI-DOCUMENT COMPARISON:</strong> Agentic document comparison workflow — upload two contracts/policies, agent identifies clause-level differences, highlights risk areas, and generates a structured comparison report with MAS/PDPA compliance flags.</li>
            <li><strong>AWS BEDROCK INTEGRATION:</strong> Deployed Claude Sonnet 3.7 via AWS Bedrock as primary inference engine; intelligent model routing — Bedrock Claude for complex reasoning, GPT-4o-mini for fast summarization — cutting API costs by <strong>38%</strong> while maintaining quality.</li>
            <li><strong>SPRING AI MICROSERVICE:</strong> Exposed RAG capabilities as a Java Spring AI microservice with typed tool definitions — existing Java enterprise systems (banking cores, ERP) call AI document analysis via standard REST/gRPC without Python dependency.</li>
            <li><strong>FINE-TUNED EMBEDDINGS:</strong> Fine-tuned HuggingFace embedding model (LoRA) on Singapore financial terminology corpus (MAS glossary, SGX reports) — improved embedding precision for domain terms by <strong>22% vs generic OpenAI</strong> embeddings.</li>
            <li><strong>MLOPS PIPELINE:</strong> MLflow experiment tracking for embedding model versions, LangSmith for RAG chain tracing, W&amp;B for retrieval quality dashboards; automated model promotion via GitLab CI with regression tests on a 500-question golden dataset.</li>
            <li><strong>RESULT:</strong> Platform processes <strong>10,000+ document pages</strong>, serves <strong>1,200+ daily queries</strong>, returns answers with source citations in under 3 seconds; deployed on Kubernetes (AWS EKS) with auto-scaling and 99.95% uptime SLA.</li>
          </ul>
